name: ConnectWise CRM REST
description: Add a ConnectWise Instance to connect your existing ConnectWise account to the crm Hub, allowing you to manage contacts , organizations and incidents across multiple Elements. You will need your ConnectWise account and ConnectWise information to add an instance.

configuration.name: ConnectWise ClientId
configuration.description: A ConnectWise clientId is a unique GUID or Globally Unique Identifier assigned to each ConnectWise integration

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: Max Page Size (or limit)
configuration.description: Connectwise REST Max Page Size (or limit)

configuration.name: Connectwise URL
configuration.description: The ConnectWise API URL to make REST API calls. For example: https://{siteUrl}/v4_6_release/apis/3.0

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

configuration.name: Time of Getting Token or Performing Authentication
configuration.description: Connectwise REST Time of Getting Token or Performing Authentication

configuration.name: Event poller refresh interval
configuration.description: Set time interval for polling application (in minutes)

configuration.name: Event Poller Resources Configuration
configuration.description: Event Poller Resources Configuration. The configuration is defined via JSON, an example of which is as follows - { "contacts": { "url": "/hubs/helpdesk/contacts", “idField”: “user.id”, “datesConfiguration”: { "updatedDateField": "user.updated_at", "updatedDateFormat": "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssX", “createdDateField”: “user.created_at”, “createdDateFormat": "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssX" }, "pageSize": 10000 } }

resources.description: Search for configurations

parameters.name: orderBy
parameters.description: Choose which field to sort the results by.(e.g. lastUpdated desc)

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression. Simple comparisons, ('=', '!=', '<', '<=', '>', '>=', 'like', 'in', 'AND', 'OR') are supported. An example query would be: lastUpdated>'2016-08-20T18:04:26Z' . To search for an array entity, append childConditions = 'true' to the request. To search for custom fields, append customConditions = 'true' to the request. A custom field query request may look like: customFields.caption='Integration' AND customConditions = 'true'

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The page number. Defaults to 1 if not provided

parameters.description: The page size. Defaults to 200 if not provided. Maximum of 2000
